      "span_text": "A study of the genes encoding hsp60, hsp70, and hsp90 revealed a significant association between loss of a specific MspI fragment in the hsp60 gene and SIDS. However, only 12 cases were investigated.  Cold stress among infants leads to increased levels of norepinephrine, which acts via ␤-adrenergic receptors to stimulate lipolysis.",
